		"body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFixes #14976 — Adds a \"Viewer and Rich Text Editor font size\" setting to the desktop app.\r\n\r\nCurrently, users can configure the Markdown editor font size, but not the viewer or Rich Text editor. This PR introduces a matching setting for those views.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n### New setting\r\n\r\n* Added `style.viewer.fontSize` support for **desktop** (previously mobile-only)\r\n* Label: **\"Viewer and Rich Text Editor font size\"**\r\n* Range: 4–50px (default: 16)\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n\r\n* `NoteEditor` and `NoteRevisionViewer` read the setting from state\r\n* Value is passed through `useMarkupToHtml` as `baseFontSize`\r\n* In `noteStyle.ts`, `baseFontSize` overrides `theme.noteViewerFontSize` when provided\r\n* This ensures consistent font sizing in:\r\n\r\n  * Markdown viewer\r\n  * Rich Text editor (TinyMCE)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n1. Open **Tools → Options → Appearance**\r\n2. Adjust **Viewer and Rich Text Editor font size**\r\n3. Confirm updates in:\r\n\r\n   * Markdown viewer\r\n   * Rich Text editor\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n* Reuses existing `style.viewer.fontSize` key (mobile) and extends it to desktop\r\n* Keeps existing behavior unchanged when the setting is not provided\r\n* Changes are scoped to font size only, without altering other styling behavior\r\n<img width=\"1520\" height=\"810\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-04-01 213637\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a99eb819-0fa5-4978-839c-332c6cbe7e69\" />\r\n<img width=\"1528\" height=\"814\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-04-01 233221\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/34519063-b255-4cd6-b5fa-d65e3eeaf875\" />\r\n",
