dependencies.|\n|**Revision Viewer** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/NoteRevisionViewer.tsx`|Added required `fontSize: number` prop, passed through `useNoteContent` into `useMarkupToHtml`.|\n|**Hook & Renderer Integration** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/hooks/useMarkupToHtml.ts`, `packages/renderer/MdToHtml.ts`, `packages/renderer/types.ts`|`useMarkupToHtml` now accepts `baseFontSize` in its dependencies and render options; renderer forwards `baseFontSize` on render and `RenderOptions` gains `baseFontSize?: number`.|\n|**CSS Generation / Styling** <br> `packages/renderer/noteStyle.ts`|`Options` gains `baseFontSize?: number`; resolved font-size used in generated CSS (body and table cell font-size).|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    actor Settings\n    participant Redux\n    participant Component\n    participant Hook as useMarkupToHtml\n    participant Renderer\n    participant noteStyle\n\n    Settings->>Redux: store style.viewer.fontSizeDesktop\n    Redux->>Component: mapStateToProps passes viewer/fontSize\n    Component->>Hook: call useMarkupToHtml(baseFontSize)\n    Hook->>Renderer: render(markup, { baseFontSize, baseFontFamily, ... })\n    Renderer->>noteStyle: noteStyle(options including baseFontSize)\n    noteStyle-->>Renderer: CSS with resolved font-size\n    Renderer-->>Hook: rendered HTML/CSS\n    Hook-->>Component: HTML assets / allAssets using baseFontSize\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 5 | ❌ 1</summary>\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 warning)\n\n|     Check name     | Status     | Explanation                                                                          | Resolution                                                                         |\n| :----------------: | :--------- | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :--------------------------------------------------